article.headline: Hampton 77, Coppin St. 69, OT
article.story: HAMPTON, Va. (AP) -- Rashad West scored 22 points and Michael Freeman added 17 on 8-for-8 shooting as Hampton beat Coppin State 77-69 in overtime Monday night. The Pirates (6-10, 3-3 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference) also got 11 points from Demario Mattox and outrebounded Coppin State 38-29. Hampton made 7 of 9 free throws in overtime after missing making just 10 of 18 in regulation. The Eagles (3-14, 1-4) got 20 points from Tywain McKee, 18 from Ruben Britt and 15 from Robert Pressey.
